-- branch-wide / folder_vap staff bypass that its sibling list views
-- (admin_files_folders_list) already have. A staff member with
-- folder_view_all / folder_vap / branch-wide admin access, but not
-- personally tagged as owner/admin/assistant on a given file (nor its
-- ancestors), fell through to the VAP+branch check at the bottom of the
-- function -- which only runs when the caller passes p_perms. Most call
-- sites for "open a file" pass p_perms = NULL, so these staff got a hard
-- `false` and the file appeared blocked ("MFN File" #341) or only
-- public/top-level files appeared to open (#344).
--
-- Fix: insert the same branches_access / folder_vap / has_vap('"'"'fd'"'"')
-- OR-branches used by admin_files_folders_list, unconditionally (not
-- gated on p_perms), right after the direct owner/admin/assistant checks
-- and before the customer-hide check -- since this is a staff-only
-- bypass, not a customer-visibility rule.

